Rock-climbing boots are an unobtainable item released along with the Grand Exchange as a joke. It is impossible to actually buy it, because the item only appears when searching the Grand Exchange, and is not an item that can actually be obtained.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • The item is a reference to a controversial update in RuneScape on 24 June 2010 where climbing boots were changed to rock climbing boots, and the price was increased from 12 coins to 75,000 coins.
  • The examine is a reference to the song These Boots Are Made for Walkin' by Nancy Sinatra.

==Trivia==
*The item is a reference to a controversial update in ''RuneScape'' on 24 June 2010 where climbing boots were changed to rock climbing boots, and the price was increased from 12 coins to 75,000 coins.
*The examine is a reference to the song ''{{wp|These Boots Are Made for Walkin'}}'' by Nancy Sinatra.
